less if you will,

38
00:02:42.870 --> 00:02:47.620
there's a chief god, Wotan,
who sees the power-laden ring, and

39
00:02:47.620 --> 00:02:51.960
for a moment he controls the world.

40
00:02:51.960 --> 00:02:54.420
He's fathered many children
with many different wives,

41
00:02:54.420 --> 00:02:59.770
including his favorite his daughter,
the rebellious Brunhilde.

42
00:02:59.770 --> 00:03:03.330
Events require Wotan to punish Brunhilde.

43
00:03:03.330 --> 00:03:07.190
Her punishment is to be
quarantined in a ring of fire.

44
00:03:07.190 --> 00:03:11.170
A ring of fire that only a super hero,
named Siegfried,

45
00:03:11.170 --> 00:03:13.640
only a super hero can penetrate.

46
00:03:13.640 --> 00:03:18.230
Siegfried does this and then he and
Brunhilde go on to further adventures and

47
00:03:18.230 --> 00:03:19.680
conflicts.

48
00:03:19.680 --> 00:03:24.950
In the end, he's killed by treachery,
and she rides into emulate

49
00:03:24.950 --> 00:03:30.310
herself in a ring of fire,
a final configuration.

50
00:03:30.310 --> 00:03:33.120
Another instance of a heroine
dying at the end of an opera.

51
00:03:34.170 --> 00:03:39.030
And in this fiery conclusion
the entire world of Wotan and

52
00:03:39.030 --> 00:03:42.260
the gods goes up and down in flames.

53
00:03:44.010 --> 00:03:47.270
To make sense of,
to pull of this together,

54
00:03:47.270 --> 00:03:53.020
nearly 17 hours of Opera,
Wagner employed a new technique.

55
00:03:53.020 --> 00:03:57.760
One using what contemporaries call
light motifs, signature motifs.

56
00:03:57.760 --> 00:04:01.270
Musical tags or musical identifiers.

57
00:04:01.270 --> 00:04:06.370
Light motifs are leading motives that
lead the listener through the opera.

